        'Open IB_01_Deal_Pipeline.xlsx in Excel for Web. Using Copilot in Excel, pull data from THREE tabs simultaneously — Live Mandates, Deal Metrics AND Fee Revenue Tracker — and build a new sheet called "Deal Triage Dashboard". On that sheet, calculate for each of the three IPO mandates: probability-weighted fee in MYR M, days to estimated close, percentage of quarter-end fee target represented, and principal execution risk. Add a group summary row at the top with KPI tiles for Total Pipeline Value MYR M, Total Probability-Weighted Fee MYR M, Mandates at Risk This Quarter, and Average Deal Velocity. Insert a horizontal bar chart of probability-weighted fee ranked by risk and a clustered column chart of deal stage versus probability score. Apply conditional formatting so mandates with close probability below 30% are red, 30% to 60% are amber, and above 60% are green. The Head of ECM presents this to the deal committee in two hours.',
        'Open IB_01_Deal_Pipeline.xlsx in Excel for Web. Using Copilot in Excel, combine data from THREE tabs — Fee Revenue Tracker, Tombstone Log AND Deal Metrics — and create a new sheet called "Revenue Vulnerability". Build a fee concentration analysis showing each deal as a percentage of total FY2026 forecast fee, a comparison of current pipeline versus historical Tombstone Log close rates, and a sensitivity table showing the fee shortfall if the top one or two mandates slip by one quarter. Add KPI tiles at the top for Top-Deal Fee Concentration %, Historical Conversion Rate vs Current Pipeline, and Maximum Downside Exposure MYR M. Insert a pie chart of fee concentration by deal and a line chart of historical quarterly close rates versus current forecast. Flag deals representing more than 60% of quarter fee as Red, 30% to 60% as Amber, and below 30% as Green. Present as a Board-pack-ready sheet.',
