        'Open TAK_01_Takaful_Portfolio.xlsx in Excel for Web. Using Copilot in Excel, cross-reference the Surplus Distribution, Participant Fund AND Wakalah Fee Tracker tabs to create a six-week decision tracker on a new sheet called "BNM Review Readiness". Show surplus ratio trend, lapse rate, wakalah fee gap versus market, Shariah exception count, and re-takaful adequacy ratio as five KPI tiles at the top. Below the tiles, build a line chart with secondary axis combining fund surplus ratio (left axis, percentage) and Shariah exception count (right axis, count) across the last eight periods. Add sparklines to each metric column so management can scan trend at a glance. Calculate whether each trend is improving, flat, or deteriorating. Flag metrics deteriorating for two or more consecutive periods as Red, one period as Amber, and stable or improving as Green. Present as a compact RAG dashboard the CEO can review weekly ahead of the BNM review.'
