        'In Outlook on the Web, click New Email then open the Copilot side pane. Use Copilot to draft an internal email to the Group CEO and Head of Shariah Governance using /TAK_01_Takaful_Portfolio.xlsx and /TAK_04_Wakalah_Fee_Benchmark.xlsx as context, explaining where the biggest fund sustainability pressure now sits, why the current wakalah fee position may no longer be defensible against digital competitors, and what strategic decisions are needed this week. Make clear what is data-backed, what remains uncertain, and what would happen to participant fund resilience if no action is taken in the next six weeks. Use the Coach my response feature to test the tone, ensure the message is factual and action-oriented, and tighten to under 200 words.',
        'In Outlook on the Web, click New Email and use Copilot to draft a formal email to governance, legal, operations, and finance stakeholders using /TAK_03_Shariah_Compliance_Policy.docx and the Surplus Distribution tab in /TAK_01_Takaful_Portfolio.xlsx as context, requesting a coordinated pre-review before the BNM governance assessment and Shariah Committee session. Highlight the three open process exceptions most at risk, the participant disclosure obligations that must be satisfied before review, and the surplus treatment questions requiring sign-off. Use Coach my response to ensure the tone is precise, constructive, and aligned with the Shariah governance register.',
